						<summary>

						<p>On a pillar in front of the <hi rend="italic">gōpura</hi> of the Śiṅgāravallabhasvāmin temple in the village.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Śaka 1348, Parābhava, Mārgaśira, śu. 2, Friday, corresponding to 1426 A.D., November 2.</p>						

						<p>Records the gift of western pillar <hi rend="italic">(bhadra)</hi> attached to the east <hi rend="italic">gōpura</hi> of the temple of Śriṅgārarāya by Nārasāni, daughter of Akkasāni.</p>						

